  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Start Fund Mexico Flood Response 2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Our main objective is to provide immediate life saving food packages, access to clean water, and health kits to 3,170 families, benefiting approximately 15,850 people that have been affected by these storms and flooding, in the municipalities of Hopelch&#xE9;n, Calakmul and Champot&#xF3;n, in the State of Campeche. 
 World Vision will work with Pro Mazahua Foundation and will provide assistance through three activities: 
  
 1) Filters for Water Purification, that will purify and enable access to safe water for the indigenous families. Furthermore, this activity will include workshops and sessions with technical training for the communities on how to adequately treat water before consumption, filter maintenance and strengthen the work previously carried out in response to COVID-19 to reinforce contingency measures. etc.) 
 
 2) Food packages for the affected population. We seek to respond immediately to the food requirements of the affected population, providing products from the market basket or minimum food basket, which will include non-perishable products such as: oil, rice, tuna, sugar, soluble coffee, cereal, jalape&#xF1;o peppers, chocolate powder, chicken broth, salad, cornstarch, flan, beans, cookies, gelatin, flour for hot cakes , laundry soap, hand soap, condensed milk, jam, toilet paper, toothpaste, soup, tomato puree, mashed potatoes, botanera sauce, etc. to mitigate and reduce the negative coping mechanism that families may have to apply 
  
  3) Health kits, in view of the COVID-19 pandemic, that will include face masks and antibacterial gel for the affected families to protect themselves.</narrative>
  </description>
